[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T17:23:01+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/polygon-mosaic-4-2.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pokemon/453190/trading-card-game-pocket-tcg-preview\"><em>Pok\u00e9mon Trading Card Game Pocket</em></a> is all about the thrill of opening digital card packs, but it has another trick up its sleeve. Released to the public on Tuesday, the mobile game has a battle mode where people can make a deck and compete against each other. For longtime Pok\u00e9mon fans who collect the cards but didn\u2019t play, it\u2019s giving them the chance to experience <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/tabletop-games/448781/pokemon-scarlet-violet-stellar-crown-tcg-preview\">competitive <em>Pok\u00e9mon TCG</em></a><em> </em>for the first time.\u00a0</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none", "id": 1425136, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pokemon/473455/tcg-pocket-battling-first-time-trading-card-game", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Many Pok\u00e9mon TCG fans have never played competitive \u2014Pocket changes that\u00a0", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T17:07:16+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/jlee_241030_1001_ptcgp_pass.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-guides\">Pok\u00e9mon TCG Pocket</a></em> has a monthly subscription called the <strong>Premium Pass</strong>. The shiny golden ticket may entice you on the home screen, but should you buy it? Is it worth buying?</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">We explain below, breaking down the math, if the <em>Pok\u00e9mon TCG Pocket</em> Premium Pass is worth buying and explain when the best time to activate your two-week free Premium Pass trial may be.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" />\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-none\"><strong>Is the Premium Pass worth buying in Pok\u00e9mon ", "id": 1425137, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-guides/473299/premium-pass-worth-it-free-trial", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Is the Pok\u00e9mon TCG Pocket Premium Pass worth buying?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T16:21:02+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Dragon Age: The Veilguard entrance to the Warden Vault\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: BioWare/Electronic Arts via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/Dragon-Age-The-Veilguard-The-Warden-Vault-cover.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">You\u2019ll find the <strong>\u201cThe Warden Vault\u201d</strong> side quest in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/dragon-age-the-veilguard/440892\">Dragon Age: The Veilguard</a></em> as you explore deeper into the <strong>Rivain Coast</strong>.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Far over on the east side of the map, you\u2019ll come across a ruined Grey Wardens castle. Inside said castle is a vault with a lot of loot \u2014 and three locks associated with puzzles nearby.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Our <em>Dragon Age: The Veilguard</em> \u201cThe Warde", "id": 1424743, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/dragon-age-veilguard-guides/471185/warden-vault-quest-walkthrough-how-to-open-locks", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to open the Warden Vault in Dragon Age: The Veilguard", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T15:55:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Mario with his hand on his cap, looking sneaky\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Nintendo\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/super-mario-odyssey-trailer.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">It just keeps happening. Nintendo keeps announcing <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/nintendo/463519/nintendo-alarmo-alarm-clock-new-hardware\">various</a> <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/472881/nintendo-music-app-android-ios\">products</a> and <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/gaming/464945/nintendo-switch-playtest-feature-theories\">projects</a> that are not the Switch 2, during the specific time period that everyone is expecting Nintendo to announce the Switch 2. Fairly or not, fans and reporters alike have been in a holding pattern since May, when Nintendo President Shuntaro Furukawa post", "id": 1424744, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/473280/nintendo-switch-2-announcement-when", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "It\u2019s becoming comical that Nintendo keeps not announcing the Switch 2", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T15:45:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/DA_EA_RookRogue.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">I\u2019m a big Dragon Age fan who has sunk hundreds of hours into the franchise, but I have a dreadful secret to admit: I\u2019ve never really enjoyed the combat. It\u2019s tedious, but tolerable; I simply go through it so I can get to that next delicious bit of story and role-playing. Imagine my surprise when I realized that <em>Dragon Age: The Veilguard</em> has combat that\u2019s an absolute blast. I\u2019m playing an Antivan Crow and a Rogue, and this game\u2019s variable settings let me live the assassin life to the fullest.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Upon starting a new game of <em>The Veilguard</em>, the player will be prompted to choose from various difficulties: Storyteller, K", "id": 1424745, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/473324/dragon-age-difficulty-options-customization-unbound", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "It&#8217;s worth tweaking Dragon Age: The Veilguard&#8217;s combat options", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T15:37:02+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/IMG_5483.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">If you have lots of duplicate cards in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-guides\">Pok\u00e9mon TCG Pocket</a></em>, you can spruce up cards with <strong>flair</strong>. These cosmetic effects are entirely optional, and just a perk for getting duplicate cards.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">You may want to snag some flair for cards, as doing so will help you complete the advanced missions for more <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-guides/471854/hourglasses-get-pack-wonder-more\">Pack Hourglasses</a>. (Though you should be able to complete the nine required missions without having to do this, as long as you do some other stuff instead.)", "id": 1424746, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-guides/469683/flair-how-to-get-shinedust-costs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__