 data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Marvel Studios\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/EAB1480_105_29851_1110_R.jpeg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Agatha All Along</em> has had a pretty clear plot setup: Agatha Harkness (Kathryn Hahn) returns to form by <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/tv/464056/witches-road-ballad-ranking-agatha-all-along\">traveling (down down down the) witches\u2019 road</a>. Along the way, she brings in coven members, old memories, unresolved wounds, and even death itself. And maybe, just maybe, that makes her a better person than she has been all along.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">[<strong>Ed. note: </strong>The rest of this post includes a spoiler warn", "id": 1423423, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/marvel/471521/agatha-all-along-season-2-release-date-cast-news", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "All the Agatha All Along season 2 news we\u2019ve heard so far", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T12:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Solas glares moodily in front of green light in Dragon Age The Veilguard\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: BioWare/Electronic Arts via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/dragon-age-beginners-guide-1.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/dragon-age-the-veilguard/440892\">Dragon Age: The Veilguard</a></em> is a sprawling RPG about battling imprisoned ancient gods, preventing all-out war between various factions and dimensions, and\u2026 kissing elves. Or dwarves. Or necromancers. To say it\u2019s complicated is an understatement.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">From character creation to navigation to combat, here are 14 things you should know before starting<em> Dragon Age: The Veilguard</em>.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-a", "id": 1422860, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/dragon-age-veilguard-guides/472235/beginners-tips-tricks-before-starting", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "14 beginner\u2019s tips to know before starting Dragon Age: The Veilguard", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T12:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Dragon Age: The Veilguard detonating a primed target\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: BioWare/Electronic Arts via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/Dragon-Age-The-Veilguard-apply-detonate-cover.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Using abilities to <strong>apply and detonate</strong> effects in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/dragon-age-the-veilguard/440892\">Dragon Age: The Veilguard</a></em> is an important step in upping your combat game. These combos combine skills from multiple characters to deal extra damage.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Our <em>Dragon Age: The Veilguard</em> combo guide will explain how to apply, prime, and detonate effects, and then we\u2019ll list all of the abilities that go into these combos.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has", "id": 1422861, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/dragon-age-veilguard-guides/472887/apply-detonate-combos-skills-how-to-all", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "All apply and detonate skill combos in Dragon Age: The Veilguard", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T12:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"All Dragon Age The Veilguard companions sit around a table in the Lighthouse\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: BioWare/Electronic Arts via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/dragon-age-veilguard-companions.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><strong>Companions</strong> are the heart and soul of <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/dragon-age-the-veilguard/440892\">Dragon Age: The Veilguard</a></em>. Recruiting these fascinating to your party happens automatically, but maintaining your relationships with each companion takes time and effort.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The most important part of that process is completing each companion\u2019s personal quest and spending enough time with them to max out their respective bond level. Strong bonds aren\u2019t just importan", "id": 1422859, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/dragon-age-veilguard-guides/472083/companions-all-list-companion-quests-party-members", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "All companions in Dragon Age: The Veilguard and how to recruit them", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T12:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Dragon Age: The Veilguard Rook standing by stairs considering how to change apperance\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: BioWare/Electronic Arts via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/dragon-age-veilguard-appearance-change.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">You can <strong>change your appearance</strong> (for free) in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/dragon-age-the-veilguard/440892\">Dragon Age: The Veilguard</a></em> as often as you like. During character creation, the game says you can change your appearance later, but it doesn\u2019t tell you when or where.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Our <em>Dragon Age: The Veilguard </em>guide to changing your appearance will tell you where to go to get a new look.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opac", "id": 1422856, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/dragon-age-veilguard-guides/470468/change-appearance-how-to-mirror-of-transformation", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to change your appearance in Dragon Age: The Veilguard", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T12:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Taash talks with one of the Lords of Fortune faction in Dragon Age The Veilguard\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: BioWare/Electronic Arts via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/dragon-age-factions.jpeg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><strong>Factions</strong> breathe political intrigue into <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/dragon-age-the-veilguard/440892\">Dragon Age: The Veilguard</a></em>, and you\u2019ll align yourself with one while creating a new character. Although you can change things like your <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/470468\">appearance</a> later on, you cannot change your faction once you\u2019ve picked one.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">For the most part, what faction you choose is mostly to do with dialogue options that are available to you, bu", "id": 1422853, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/dragon-age-veilguard-guides/469867/best-faction-choice-which-all", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to choose the best faction for you in Dragon Age: The Veilguard", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T12:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"All romance options in Dragon Age The Veilguard stand next to each other in a graphic\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Graphic: Polygon | Source images: BioWare/Electronic Arts\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/dragon-age-veilguard-romance.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><strong>Romance</strong> has always been a big draw in Dragon Age games, and <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/dragon-age-the-veilguard/440892\">Dragon Age: The Veilguard</a></em> is no different. As Rook, you have seven <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/472083\">companions</a> in <em>The Veilguard</em>, and all of them are potential romance partners. While you might be excited to jump right to flirting, there are a few wrinkles in the romance system that are worth considering.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-alig", "id": 1422858, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/dragon-age-veilguard-guides/471892/romance-options-all-how-to-romance-characters", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to romance characters in Dragon Age: The Veilguard", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T12:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Dragon Age: The Veilguard meeting the Antivan Crows in Treviso\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: BioWare/Electronic Arts via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/Dragon-Age-The-Veilguard-Treviso-or-Dock-Town.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><strong>Dock Town</strong>\u2019s \u201cThe Smuggled Relic Case\u201d and <strong>Treviso</strong>\u2019s \u201cSea of Blood\u201d are a pair of <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/dragon-age-the-veilguard/440892\">Dragon Age: The Veilguard</a></em> main story quests you\u2019ll pick up after completing \u201cThe Singing Blade.\u201d Once you talk to Neve, you\u2019ll get the \u201cInto the Crossroads\u201d quest along with \u201cSea of Blood\u201d and \u201cThe Smuggled Relic Case.\u201d</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">You next step is to travel to either <strong>Dock Town </strong>or <strong>Treviso <", "id": 1422855, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/dragon-age-veilguard-guides/470287/dock-town-treviso-sea-of-blood-smuggled-relic-case", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Should you go to Dock Town or Treviso first in Dragon Age: The Veilguard?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T12:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Dragon Age: The Veilguard a blighted dragon attacking\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: BioWare/Electronic Arts via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/Dragon-Age-The-Veilguard-dragon-choice-2.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><strong>\u201cOn Deadly Wings\u201d </strong>is the <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/dragon-age-the-veilguard/440892\">Dragon Age: The Veilguard</a></em> quest you\u2019ll get immediately after returning to the Lighthouse with Darvin, your griffon-guarding <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/472083\">companion</a>, in tow. The rest of the crew meets you and tells you about a pair of dragons attacking Minrathous and Treviso, and you\u2019ll have to save one city or the other.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Our <em>Dragon Age: The Veilguard</em> guide will h", "id": 1422857, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/dragon-age-veilguard-guides/470597/minrathous-treviso-save-choice-on-deadly-wings", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Should you save Minrathous or Treviso in Dragon Age: The Veilguard?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-31T12:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Dragon Age: The Veilguard party meeting the mayor of D\u2019Meta\u2019s Crossing\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: BioWare/Electronic Arts via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/Dragon-Age-The-Veilguard-dmeta-mayor-1.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=27.6,0,56.320001220703,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">During the <strong>\u201cShadows Crossing\u201d</strong> <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/dragon-age-the-veilguard/440892\">Dragon Age: The Veilguard</a> </em>main story quest, you\u2019ll explore the blighted town of <strong>D\u2019Meta\u2019s Crossing</strong>. At the end of the quest, yo